Since localisation support it is an experimental feature that may not
work. You can try to create localisation here are using same method to
generate localisation files. Here is a file 'locales', in current
folder. Which hold a list of experimental locales.
> make
Just run make, and it's create quiet process of building patcher,
creation of localisation for system environment, and applying patch to
it, to be compatible with glibc locale file version.
